Rule Name: explain-command-and-flags

When showing any shell/CLI command, always provide:
- A short, plain-English summary describing what the command does.
- A brief explanation of each flag used in the command.
- Keep explanations clear and concise.

Optional: To add this rule to your project using `.cursorrules`:
- Create a `.cursorrules` file at the project root and add:
  - For any shell/CLI command shown, also provide:
    - A short plain-English summary of what it does.
    - A brief explanation of each flag.
    - Keep explanations concise and non-jargony.

